1) Building with configure script (recommended)
===============================================
    $ ./configure
    $ make
    $ make install

If you do not have the root privilege, specify 'prefix' argument
to configure script (prefix=/usr/local, by default).

    $ ./configure prefix=(somewhere you can install)


2) Building without configure script
====================================

Without configure script, you should create a Makefile manually.
Copy 'Makefile.freebsd-i386' and modify it for your system.
Consult 'config.h.in'.

    $ cp Makefile.freebsd-i386 Makefile.YOURSYS-YOURARCH
    $ vi Makefile.YOURSYS-YOURARCH
    $ make -f Makefile.YOURSYS-YOURARCH
    $ make -f Makefile.YOURSYS-YOURARCH install
